Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Goleta Beach Park
Description: Known for its long fishing pier and sunbathing beaches. These 29 acres are often a destination for bicyclists on the area's paved trail system.

Name: More Mesa Beach
Description: More Mesa Beach is a narrow beach hidden away below the bluffs of More Mesa Park in Santa Barbara. Due to its seclusion it has a reputation as a clothing-optional beach.

Name: Santa Barbara Shores Park
Description: A natural area, this park is still under development. Presently there exist hiking trails over coastal bluffs and through thick eucalyptus groves.

Name: Inspiration Point
Description: Inspiration Point is a 3.5 mile heavily trafficked out and back trail that offers the chance to see wildlife and is rated as moderate.

Name: Santa Barbara County Superior Court
Description: The Santa Barbara County Courthouse is a signature building structure in the city of Santa Barbara. It is built in the Spanish Colonial style and was built in 1929 and still functions as a working courthouse.
